HEADWORD: Insensuous
<hw>In*sen"su*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>sensuous</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not sensuous; not
pertaining to, affecting, or addressing, the senses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That intermediate door⟦br⟧
Betwixt the different planes of sensuous form⟦br⟧
And form <qex>insensuous</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

